    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nOriginal issue:\n- https://github.com/nvim-mini/mini.nvim/issues/2283#issuecomment-3959086679\n\nWhen `vim._core.ui2` is enabled, `nvim_exec 'highlight'` produces incorrect output after the second time `nvim_exec` is called. The spacing between `SpecialKey` and `xxx` is missing.\n\n> The first \"line\" is as expected: `SpecialKey     xxx links to Special`\n> The first \"line\" is not as expected: `SpecialKeyxxx links to Special`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vim\nnvim --clean\n:lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({})\n:lua vim.api.nvim_exec2('map', { output = true })\n:= vim.api.nvim_exec2('highlight', { output = true }).output --[[Invalid output]]\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```vim\n:= vim.api.nvim_exec2('highlight', { output = true }).output\n```\n\nshould always output\n\n```\nSpecialKey     xxx links to Special\n```\n\ninstead of\n\n```\nSpecialKeyxxx links to Special\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2412+g6d73bf4886\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.16.1 (42f49eeb)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\n[MordechaiHadad/bob](https://github.com/MordechaiHadad/bob)",
